DPRK Founding Anniversary Celebrated Abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 5 (KCNA) -- A celebration meeting was held by the Party for Peace and Unity of Russia on August 31on the occasion of the 56th anniversary of the foundation of the DPRK.
 Chairperson of the party S. Z. Umalatova said in a report that with the foundation of the DPRK the political situation of East Asia had been radically changed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the leadership of President Kim Il Sung the protracted struggle of the Korean people to liberate the country from the Japanese occupiers was concluded with victory and a genuine people's country was built in the land of Korea, so that the road of socialist development was opened in this region. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has covered the road of new development under the leadership of Kim Jong Il, a great successor to the idea and cause of Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Through the Russia visit of Kim Jong Il not only the Russian people but the whole world have come to know clearly that he is steering the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK is now displaying its might as a powerful socialist country which has the people single-heartedly united around the leader and the invincible revolutionary armed forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers praised the state building exploits of Kim Il Sung and the Songun leadership exploits of Kim Jong Il. They stressed that new victories and successes are always in store for the DPRK and the Korean people invariably holding high the socialist banner. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A message of greetings to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, a round-table talk, a lecture and a film show were held by the Trunov County Committee of the Communist Party of Bohemia and Moravia of the Czech Republic, the commercial faculty of the Makerere University in Uganda and a machine company in Indonesia from August 27 to 31.

U.S. Moves for Preemptive Attack under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 5 (KCNA) -- The United States is now massively deploying its aggression armed forces in the Asia-Pacific region surrounding the Korean peninsula under the pretext of "promptly countering" hotspots around the globe. This goes to prove that the U.S. ambition for world supremacy to occupy strategic vantages in Northeast Asia and the world's main natural resource areas on the plea of "combating terror" is entering the full-fledged practice.
 Rodong Sinmun Sunday says this in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is working hard to form a "rapid reaction force" in the Asia-Pacific region to contain China and Russia and create a favorable circumstance for the realization of its strategy for world domination in the new century. Considering the Korean peninsula as its key link in carrying out its Asia-Pacific strategy the U.S. intends to make it a test ground for its "long distance attack strategy" and "rapid mobile operation". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. bellicose forces have planned to move the First U.S. Army Corps Command to Japan and most of the U.S. troops in south Korea from the areas of the Military Demarcation Line to deploy them south of the River Han. This is aimed to further increase the capabilities of preemptive attack on the DPRK with its naval and air force, "rapid reaction force," etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is foolish for the U.S. to realize its design for domination in the Korean peninsula and the Asia-Pacific region with the "rapid reaction force." The U.S. is grossly mistaken if it thinks that it will be safe with others suffering from damage as it launches a "rapid maneuvers" with its "long distance attack strategy". Ultra-modern equipment is not monopoly of the U.S. There is no limit in the striking force of the Korean People's Army. If the U.S. dare ignite a war against the DPRK, misjudging its might, the aggressors will not evade a merciless retaliatory strike anywhere they may be.

"History of Anti-Japanese Armed Struggle" Vol. 6 Published 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 5 (KCNA) -- The Science and Encyclopedia Press has brought out book "History of Anti-Japanese Armed Struggle" (enlarged edition) vol. 6.
 The book carries the immortal fighting feats performed by President Kim Il Sung in leading the whole Korean revolution centering on the anti-Japanese armed struggle to a great upswing by wisely leading the Korean People's Revolutionary Army and party and revolutionary organizations in the historic period from late autumn of Juche 25 (1936) to late June of Juche 26 (1937). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It says that the President put forward the policy of frustrating the "winter great punitive" offensive of the Japanese imperialists and consolidating the Mt. Paektu base at the military and political cadres meeting of the Korean People's Revolutionary Army held in November Juche 25 (1936) and then wisely led the struggle to this end. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He led to a brilliant victory the operation of advance into the homeland with the historic Pochonbo battle as the main and rapidly expanded party organizations and the Association for the Restoration of the Fatherland to immensely strengthen the revolutionary forces on a nationwide scale, the book adds.

Czech Organization Denounces Ulji Focus Lens-04 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 4 (KCNA) -- The Paektusan Czech-Korean Friendship Association made public a statement denouncing the U.S.-south Korea joint military exercise Ulji Focus Lens-04 on Aug. 31.
 The statement said that the aim of Ulji Focus Lens-04 is to complete the preparations for starting any moment a war similar to the Korean war that broke out in 1950. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This kind of military exercise has been periodically staged against the DPRK for the last more than decade along with economic sanctions and smear campaigns, the statement noted, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This military exercise can never go with dialogue for seeking a peaceful settlement of the nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a grave one of chilling the atmosphere of dialogue and harassing peace. It goes to clearly prove that the U.S. is chiefly responsible for blocking peace and reunification of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. is interested in defusing the tensions and ensuring peace in Korea and wants dialogue, it should immediately stop the military exercise in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We demand the U.S. drop its hostile policy towards the DPRK and withdraw its armed forces from south Korea.

Struggle for Frustrating GNP's Plot Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 4 (KCNA) -- The Information Department of the Central Committee of the National Democratic Front of south Korea on September 2 made public an appeal calling upon the south Korean people from all walks of life to turn out in the struggle for frustrating the plot of the Grand National Party (GNP) to foil the movement for probe into the truth about past history, according to Kuguk Jonson Internet site.
 The appeal said: The GNP worked hard to foil the movement for probe into truth about past history from its outset. When it has become a trend of the times to demand the liquidation of past history, the GNP let loose sheer sophism that "pro-north and pro-communist activities" should be included in the objects to be probed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The aim of the GNP is nothing but to groundlessly link the movement with the north in a bid to divert the probe elsewhere and cover up its crime-woven history in which its gang committed pro-Japanese acts of treachery and pro-U.S. sycophantic acts, enforced fascist dictatorship,practiced corruption, pursued confrontation with the north and did harm to fellow countrymen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The far-fetched assertion made by the GNP is aimed to brand the patriots of all social strata who have worked for national reconciliation, cooperation and reunification and the people desirous of national reunification in this land as "pro-north and pro-communist elements." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The people from all walks of life should turn out in an all-people struggle to liquidate the past history in order to completely eliminate the traitorous party just as they punished the GNP during the presidential election and the National Assembly election. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the people and the organizations of the anti-U.S. movement should conduct the struggle to probe the truth behind the past history in close combination with the struggle to frustrate the U.S. colonial rule over south Korea and interference in its internal affairs, the appeal concluded.

U.S.-S. Korea Joint War Exercise under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 4 (KCNA) -- The U.S. and the south Korean bellicose forces staged Ulji Focus Lens-04 joint military drill from August 23 to eptember 3.
 Rodong Sinmun Saturday in a signed commentary carried in this regard says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was a preliminary war and a test nuclear war aimed to put into practice the "operation plan 5027-04," a new war scenario worked out by the U.S. imperialist warmongers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ulji Focus Lens-04 fully disclosed that it was of the same aggressive and provocative nature as that of "team spirit" joint exercise in its purpose and content. It was an extremely adventurous maneuver for a war of aggression presupposing a preemptive nuclear attack on the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists are persistently insisting that the DPRK scrap its nuclear program first, backtracking on the principle "words for words", "action for action" and "reward for freeze" publicly recognized by the international community. They are openly heading for a provocative military option, beclouding the prospect of the peaceful settlement of the nuclear issue between the DPRK and the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. staged the joint military exercise in a bid to threaten and pressurize the DPRK by force of arms and, at the same time, achieve its criminal purpose of igniting a nuclear war at any cost on the Korean peninsula under the pretext of the nuclear issue between them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Herein lies the danger of the recent joint military exercise which should not be overlooked. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean authorities staged such dangerous north-targeted saber-rattling in collusion with the outside forces in violation of the spirit of the June 15 joint declaration, thus inciting distrust and confrontation between the north and the south and laying a stumbling block in the way of improving the north-south relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. and its followers should act with discretion, pondering over the catastrophic consequences to be entailed by their anachronistic hostile policy toward the DPRK and moves for inciting confrontation between the north and the south.

Reception Given by Malaysian Ambassador
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 4 (KCNA) -- Malaysian Ambassador e. p. to the DPRK MD.Yusoff Bin MD. Zain gave a reception Friday evening on the occasion of the 47th Malaysian national day.
 Present on invitation were Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, Kim Yong Il, Choe Su Il, officials concerned, foreign diplomatic envoys and representatives of international organizations here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were staff members of the Malaysian embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the reception.

Agricultural Workers' Traditional Sports Games Open
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 4 (KCNA) -- The 4th national agricultural workers' traditional sports games opened on the occasion of the 56th anniversary of the DPRK.
 The games brought together over 500 players of 10 units selected at the provincial, city and county competitions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants will compete in Korean wrestling, Taekwon-Do, seesaw, swinging, yut-game, chess and tug-of-war on the knockout basis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An opening ceremony was held at the recreation ground of Rungra Islet.
 Then followed Taekwon-Do matches.

Pyongyang Art Troupe Performs in China
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Beijing, September 2 (KCNA) -- The Pyongyang Art Troupe that had participated in the 6th Asian Art Festival held in China gave its performances in Beijing, Changchun and Yanji of Jilin Province and Harbin of Heilongjiang Province from August 19 to 31 before full houses.
 The art performances were appreciated by senior officials of the capital city and local areas and people from all walks of life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meng Xiaosi, vice-minister of the Chinese Ministry of Culture, said dance "Peasant dances" presented by the art troupe clearly showed the feature of flourishing Korean arts and it added to the festive atmosphere. He went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Frequent art exchanges with the DPRK are very important not only for the development of arts in Asia but for boosting the friendship between the DPRK and China. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A producer of the Tungfang Song and Dance Ensemble said that the "Peasant dances" are a gem like work as they played a key role in the whole course of the festival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As we clearly realized through a series of visits of our ensemble to the DPRK, its arts have admirable progress under the correct leadership of Kim Jong Il who is well versed in arts. I would like to visit Korea frequently to study the Korean performing art. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The councilor at the Ministry of Culture noted that the "Peasant dances" were acclaimed by the audience for their distinct national flavour and very dynamic and unique movements. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The vice-chairman of the Chinese Association of Producers said that the Korean national arts are wonderful as they are peculiar and splendid and meet the sentiment of the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chief of the Yanbian Branch of the Chinese People's Bank had this to say: The performance given by the Korean artistes helped the audience feel refreshed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A dance "A flower I love" made so truthful representation that the audience felt as if they had seen real flowers in full bloom on the stage. I think the flowers reflected the world people's praises of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The honorary chairman of the Yanbian Association of Artists said that the Korean folk songs "Yangsando", "Song of bean paste", "Let's go to the Kwanghan Pavilion" and others completely gripped the hearts of the audience for beautiful voices, a high level of representation, natural response to the audience and refined high talents of performers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The general manager of the Heilongjiang Production Company said that the Pyongyang Art Troupe is loved by the audience as it deeply touched them with peculiar attraction.

Memorial Services Held in Japan
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tokyo, September 2 (KNS-KCNA) -- A memorial service was held in front of the monument to the Korean victims in Tokyo on Sept. 1, 81 years since the assacre of Koreans after the Kanto quake in 1923.
 Pak Yun Gi, vice-chairman of the Tokyo Metropolitan Headquarters of Chongryon (General Association of Korean Residents in Japan), in his memorial address said that when a great quake occurred in Kanto in 1923, the Japanese authorities committed such thrice-cursed atrocities as hurling army and police forces and even civilians to kill thousands of Koreans in cold blood after setting afloat a rumor. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Although 81 years have passed since then the right-wing reactionaries and media in Japan are still misleading the public opinion, stoking hostility toward the DPRK and creating a terror-ridden atmosphere to incriminate Koreans in Japan, he said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He urged the Japanese authorities to sincerely implement the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration and called on the compatriots to achieve national reunification, their cherished desire, without fail so that they might discharge their mission as the descendent of the victims. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Representatives of youth and students spoke next. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They said that they would never forget the bitter grudge of the victims, protect the dignity of the nation and give full play to its resourcefulness. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A figure of the Tokyo Metropolitan Assembly who attended the service begged Koreans' forgiveness for killing Koreans for no understandable reason and assured those present there that the similar tragedy would never occur. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants observed a moment's silence in memory of the victims. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Memorial services were also held in Chiba and Saitama Prefectures under the sponsorship of the headquarters and branches of Chongryon on the same day.

Message of Sympathy to Russian President
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 4 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, Saturday sent a message of sympathy to Vladimir Vladimirovich Putin, president of the Russian Federation, in connection with the recent explosions and hostage-taking incident in Russia perpetrated by terrorists that caused huge casualties among innocent inhabitants.
 The message said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A chain of recent hideous terrorism in your country can never be justified as they were the dastardly criminal acts perpetrated by the separatist forces and international terrorists to foil the process of the political settlement of the Chechen issue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The government of our Republic, which has maintained the consistent stand of opposing all forms of terrorism, fully supports all the steps taken by the Russian government to settle the terrorist cases and ensure the territorial integrity of the country and believes that the Russian government will eradicate the aftermath of terrorist acts as soon as possible and achieve the stability and unity of the country under your leadership.

Foreign Ministry Spokesman on Recent Terrorism in Russia
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 4 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the DPRK Foreign Ministry gave the following answer to a question put by KCNA Saturday in connection with a series of recent terrorist acts in Russia that caused huge casualties:
 The terrorist acts committed in different parts of Russia recently have greatly shocked and infuriated the international community. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As already reported, two airliners crashed in the air above Rostov and Tula regions on August 24 due to suicide bomb attacks. On August 31 a bomb explosion ripped through an entrance of a subway station in Moscow, claiming big casualties. 
 On September 1 terrorists occupied a middle school in the Republic of Northern Osetia when a ceremony of the new school year was under way and held hundreds of students and their parents and teachers hostage. This terrorism claimed big casualties. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A series of terrorist acts committed in different regions of Russia before and after the recent election of the Chechen president were targeted against innocent civilians, children in particular. They were base and hideous terrorism perpetrated by separatist forces and international terrorists linked to them in a bid to derail the process of a political settlement in Chechnya, create uneasiness and terror among Russians and thus violate the territorial integrity in Russia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the consistent and fixed stand of the DPRK government to oppose all forms of terrorism and any aid to it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Proceeding from this stand, the DPRK has actively supported the measures taken by the Russian government to cleanse Chechen terrorists and protect the security and territorial integrity of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK strongly denounces recent terrorism in Russia and extends full solidarity to the government and people of Russia in all their efforts to eradicate the aftermath of terrorism at an early date and ensure lasting stability and territorial integrity of the country.
